Approach 6: At n=5, V(F)={a,b,c}, V(D)={a,b,x}, external d
d must be external to D, so d not in {a,b,x}.
d is either c or the 5th vertex y.
If d = c: d in V(F), at-risk = {a,b,c,x} = 4, good = 1.
If d = y (5th vertex): at-risk = {a,b,c,x,y} = 5, good = 0.
So we need: for SOME (F,D) pair, d in V(F) OR |dom(D)|>=2.
Equivalently: NOT all (F,D) pairs have d = y (5th vertex) and |dom|=1.

  ALL (F,D) pairs have d outside V(F)uV(D): 240
  SOME pairs have d outside: 0
  => 240 tournaments where Lemma B gives 0 guaranteed good
